                        "title": "New constitution in two weeks: Minister Basnet",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minister for Industry Mahesh Basnet has said that a new constitution would be issued within two weeks and it would win the hearts of all.\r\n\r\nSpeaking at the best education award distribution programme organized by Nepal Civil Servants Organization under the Ministry of Education in the capital today, Minister Basnet said that the new constitution with delineation of border of the federal provinces would be issued soon on the consensus of all as the constitution drafting process was in final phase.\r\n\r\nHe pointed out the need of alienating the border with considering the geography of hilly, mountainous and terai belts though some Madhes-centric leaders were involving in foul playing.\r\nHe added that some forces were involving in foul playing as it could disintegrate the national sovereignty.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, Minister Basnet pointed out the need of developing the quality of education as over three million students were in abroad and the country was surviving through the remittance sent by them.\r\n\r\nHe further added that the education sectors will remain as only unemployment generating system unless the coordination would be made in budgetary system between the Ministries of Education and Industry.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, secretary at the Ministry of Education Bishwa Prakash Pandit said that the school dropping ratio of the students was not lessening though they were enhancing the quality of education. On the occasion, Minister Basnet and Secretary Pandit jointly launched a souvenir prepared by the union.\r\n\r\nShreeya Poudel, Sagar Sunuwar, Soniya Gautam and Pragyan Gautam were each awarded with Rs 5,000. They were the highest scorers in the school leaving certificate examination of 2071 from among the children of civil servants.</p>",
