                        "id": 19074,
                        "title": "Secularism should be removed from new constitution: NC leader Koirala",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/news_733769385.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-19076\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/news_733769385.jpg\" alt=\"news_733769385\" width=\"260\" height=\"260\" /></a>Nepali Congress Central Working Committee member and lawmaker Dr Shashank Koirala has pointed out the need of removing the word secularism from the new constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">While launching a magazine Sankalpa at a discussion programme related to the context of upcoming general assembly of the party in Pokhara, leader Koirala said that the secularism should be displaced by religious freedom.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He added that the religion and nationality should not be politicized. Speaking in another context, leader Koirala expressed his dissatisfaction on the growing factionalism in the party.</p>",
