                    {
                        "id": 19016,
                        "title": "बेहोस भई अस्पताल भर्ना भएका  नेपालको स्वास्थ्यमा सुधार, मंगलबार डिस्चार्ज ",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/madhav1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-19017\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/madhav1.jpg\" alt=\"madhav\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" /></a>सोमबार अचानक रक्तचाप वृद्धि भई अस्वस्थ भएपछि वीर अस्पताल ‘ट्रमा सेन्टर’मा  भर्ना हुनुभएका नेकपा (एमाले) का नेता माधवकुमार नेपालको स्वाथ्यमा सुधार आएको अस्पतालले जनाएको छ ।\r\n\r\nव्यवस्थापिका–संसद्को बैठकमा सहभागी रहेकै बेला हाजिर पुस्तिकामा हाजिर गर्दा गर्दै असजिलो महसुस भएपछि पूर्वप्रधानमन्त्री नेपाललाई तत्कालै अस्पताल लगिएको उहाँका सहयोगी मोहन गौतमले जानकारी दिनुभयो ।\r\n\r\nनेपालको ईसीजी, सिटी स्क्यान लगायतका अन्य परिक्षण गरिएको चिकित्सा विज्ञान राष्ट्रिय प्रतिष्ठान (न्याम्स) का उपकुलपति प्रा. डा. गणेश गुरुङ्गले बताए | गुरुङ्गले नेपालको  डिस्चार्ज मंगलबार नै हुने जनाए |</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/madhav1.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-28 05:59:27",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/19016"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18978,
                        "title": "No compromise on norms and values of democracy: PM Koirala",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prime Minister Sushil Koirala has said that there would be no compromise in the norms and values of the democracy in course of drafting the new constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/pm1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18979\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/pm1.jpg\" alt=\"Mukta Kamaya, Kamlari and Halia submits memorandum  to the PM\" width=\"839\" height=\"548\" /></a></p>\r\nReleasing a biannual report of the National Information Commission at a function held at his official residence at Baluwatar today, Prime Minister Koirala reiterated that there would be no compromise in the norms and values of democracy as all have accepted democracy. \"We will move ahead incorporating thoughts and suggestions of all by making the democracy as the basis in course of constitution writing. A concept that the government is servant of people in democracy will be established,” he said.\r\n\r\nStating that people working with commitment would never be unsuccessful, PM Koirala urged the Commission to move ahead with confidence to establish peoples rights to information.\r\n\r\nHe further said that all information except on five issues including national security, should be given to people as well as information regarding good deeds and weaknesses of the government should be made public.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, Minister for Information and Communications, Dr Minendra Rijal, said that the government would provide continuous support to the Commission in this regard. \"Give information in protection of democracy in a transparent manner but keep secrecy on the issue of national interest\", he said.\r\n\r\nLikewise, Chief Commissioner at the Commission, Krishna Hari Banskota, said that suggestion has been given for the provision of rights to information dissemination in the draft of the new constitution saying the trend of hiding information in the name of secrecy should be ended.",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/pm1.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-27 08:53:58",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18978"
                    },
