                        "id": 18910,
                        "title": "CA should be dissolved if constitution continues to remain in limbo: Mahara",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/mahara.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-18911\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/mahara.jpg\" alt=\"mahara\" width=\"192\" height=\"240\" /></a>UCPN (Maoist) General Secretary Krishna Bahadur Mahara has stressed on the need to promulgate the new constitution on time.\r\n\r\nWhile addressing a programme organized by the National Christian Federation, leader Mahara said that the constituent assembly (CA) might be nullified if constitution promulgation remained in limbo. He added that his party was first to fight against the state favored religion.\r\n\r\nHe said that the state should not have a particular religion. Leader Mahara added that his party has a special role to institutionalize the different agendas of the various peoples movements.\r\nOn the occasion, Law expert Chandra Kant Gyawali and former attorney general Mukti Pradhan pointed out the need of clearly mentioning religious freedom or secularism in the new constitution.</p>",
