                        "id": 18746,
                        "title": "Pushpa Lals contribution unforgettable: UML chair Oli",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">CPN (UML) chairman KP Sharma Oli, has said that Nepal Communist party founder general secretary Pushpa Lal Shresthas contribution to the Nepali Communist movement was unforgettable.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/kpoli2.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18762\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/kpoli2.jpg\" alt=\"Oli Delivers Remarks\" width=\"839\" height=\"543\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Speaking in programme organized to mark the 37th memorial day of the late leader in the capital, chair Oli said that Shrestha was a leading figure in Nepal politics who fought against feudalism in Nepal.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He added that the UML has gone ahead by assimilating the principles of leader Shrestha and it has helped the party to be competitive, progressive and anti feudalist during 66 years of communist partys establishment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Chairman Oli added that a new constitution would be issued very soon as the country has gone through eight years ups and downs after the establishment of republicanism in the country. The new constitution would institutionalize the different achievements of people’s movements, he said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Similarly Pushpa Lal Memorial Foundation chair and party leader Madhav Kuamr Nepal said that Pushpa Lals thought was equally relevant to these days as it was in the past.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He added that the co-work between leftist and Nepali Congress was essential even to the prosperity of the nation as such co-work has succeeded the various peoples movements in the past. He added that they had published the leader Pushpa Lals historical documents even to make them alive.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On the occasion, chair Oli, leader Nepal, party Vice-chair and Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Home Affairs Bamdev Gautam, general secretary Ishwor Pokharel among other leaders offered garlands on the statue of late leader Shrestha.</p>",
