                        "title": "Discussion over draft constitution-- security strengthened",
                        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/bicc4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-18518\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/bicc4.jpg\" alt=\"bicc\" width=\"275\" height=\"183\" /></a>The District Administration Office and political parties in Saptari district today held discussion in Rajbiraj regarding collection of feedback of people on the draft of the new constitution to be held on July 20 and 21.\r\n\r\nDuring the meeting held at residence of the Chief District Officer, they discussed to provide security to lawmakers and employees deployed in course of feedback collection.\r\n\r\nChief District Officer, Birendra Yadav, said that feedback would be collected on draft constitution in Constituencies 1, 2 and 3 on July 20 and formal discussion on it in constituencies 4, 5 and 6.\r\n\r\nThe Madhesi Front, that has been venting its dissatisfaction over the draft constitution, did not participate in todays meeting while local intellectuals, chiefs of different security bodies, civil society and media persons were present.",
