                    {
                        "id": 19272,
                        "title": "Leader Deuba meets Indian President Mukherjee",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/deuba-mukarjee.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-19285\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/deuba-mukarjee.jpg\" alt=\"deuba-mukarjee\" width=\"728\" height=\"506\" /></a>Former Prime Minister and senior leader of the Nepali Congress, Sher Bahadur Deuba, met with President of India, Pranab Mukherjee, today.</p>\r\nPolitical Minister Counselor at the Nepali Embassy in New Delhi, Tirtha Wagle, told the National News Agency (RSS) that during the meeting they discussed on mutual interests and welfare of both countries and the latest political scenario of Nepal. The meeting took place at 1:30 pm at the Office of the President in New Delhi.\r\n\r\nOn the occasion, leader Deuba lauded the support provided by India to Nepal after the quake. Before this, leader Deuba had held meetings with Minister of Ecternal Affairs of India, Sushma Swaraj, and Indian Foreign Secretary S Jaishanker.\r\n\r\nFormer PM Deuba has left here on Wednesday on a week-long India visit at the invitation of the Indian government.",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/deuba-mukarjee.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-31 11:33:53",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/19272"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 19066,
                        "title": "Draft of new constitution should be rewrite: Chair Yadav",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/upendra-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-17243\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/upendra-1.jpg\" alt=\"upendra (1)\" width=\"198\" height=\"255\" /></a>Chairman of the Federal Socialist Forum Nepal, Upendra Yadav, has said that draft of the new constitution should be rewritten for making the new constitution acceptable to all.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At a news conference organised at Birtamod in Jhapa district today, Chairman Yadav expressed the view that it would not be acceptable to them if this draft was promulgated as the new constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He further said that the new constitution should guarantee federalism along with provincial autonomy, identity, inclusion, republicanism, secularism and end of discrimination.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Chair Yadav said, \"The draft of the new constitution is against previous agreement, sentiments and process of the Constituent Assembly (CA).\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stating that the new statute should be issued from the CA, he said it would not be acceptable to the people if leaders of some parties tried to promulgate the new constitution without finalizing the contentious issues in their bid to be Prime Minister and President, neglecting the CA regulations and process.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On a different note, Chairman Yadav said that secularism would not be changed as it has already been established from peoples movement 2062/63 BS.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/upendra.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-28 10:34:17",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/19066"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 19033,
                        "title": "PM Koirala condoles death of APJ Abdul Kalam",
                        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/APJ-Abdul-Kalam.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-19034\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/APJ-Abdul-Kalam.jpg\" alt=\"APJ-Abdul-Kalam\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" /></a>Prime Minister Sushil Koirala has expressed deep sorrow over the demise of India’s former President APJ Abdul Kamal. India’s former President Kamal died last night at the age of 84.\r\n\r\n“I am saddened to hear the news of passing away of Kamal,” said PM Koirala.\r\n\r\nIn a message, PM Koirala has expressed his condolence to Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Government of India, relatives of Kamal and the Indian people on behalf of the government and people of Nepal and on his own in this hour of grief.\r\n\r\nPM Koirala has also recalled Kalam’s contributions to lead India in the path of scientific advancement and progress.\r\n\r\n“Nepal has lost a good friend and I have lost an honoured and ideal personality,” PM Koirala said.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, Prime Minister Sushil Koirala has condemned the cowardly terrorist attack on a police station and a public vehicle at Gurdaspur in the Indian state of Punjab. Five police personnel and three civilians were killed in the Gurdaspur terror strike on Monday morning.\r\n\r\nIn a message, PM Koirala has condemned the cowardly and inhuman attack and said that Nepal Government and the people of Nepal were with India in this hour.\r\n\r\nPM Koirala has expressed his condolence to the security personnel and relatives of civilians killed in the terrorist attack, and the Indian people on behalf of the government and people of Nepal.\r\n\r\nPM Koirala has stressed the need for working together to defeat terrorism as it was against peace, stability, democracy and development.",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/APJ-Abdul-Kalam.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-28 06:12:08",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/19033"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18908,
                        "title": "Hindus urge Australia’s Liverpool Council not to serve beef at interfaith lunch",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-17887\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg\" alt=\"zed8-300x178\" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" /></a>Hindus are urging to keep beef off the menu of interfaith lunches and dinners of Liverpool (a Sydney suburb) City Council.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada (USA) today, said that cow was held sacred by Hindus and was considered the seat of many deities. Consuming beef was considered sacrilegious among Hindus.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With its population increasingly diverse, Liverpool Council should be respectful to all the faith traditions while deciding menu for interfaith lunches and dinners; as purpose of interfaith gatherings was to bring diverse traditions to sit and eat together in fellowship displaying harmonious coexistence, Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, noted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed further said that Liverpool Council should walk the talk and seriously follow its own tagline which stated \"creating our future together\" and its own Guiding Principle of \"We will be fair and just\".</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Per Council’s website, Liverpool’s 40% population is born overseas in over 150 countries, with Fiji and India being among the top ten. Liverpool residents speak over 140 different languages and about half of its residents speak language other than English at home (Hindi being among the top ten). Hinduism has increased in Liverpool since 2006.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ned Mannoun, Gus Ballout and Carl Wulff are Mayor, Deputy Mayor and CEO of City Council of Liverpool, which was “founded” in 1810. Prominent people associated with Liverpool include: cricketer Michael Clarke, Olympic swimmer Michael Wenden, footballer Mark Bosnich and entertainer Nathan Foley.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-26 11:18:21",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18908"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18872,
                        "title": "Directly elected executive head must for political stability",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/singha-durbar.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-15472\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/singha-durbar.jpg\" alt=\"singha-durbar\" width=\"650\" height=\"433\" /></a>CPN Uml And UCPN (Maoist) on Saturday underscored the need for directly elected executive head for the stability in countrys politics.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Speaking at an interaction on Directly Elected Executive System organized in Lalitpur, Dr  Baburam Bhattarai said it was necessary to incorporate a provision for a directly elected head of the government in order to address Nepal’s specialty and relativity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He called for institutionalizing the achievements gained from Nepali peoples sacrifice. Bhattarai charged that the political parties had failed to rise above personal and party interests while insisting on the urgency for streamlining the management of the countrys political system and the states operating mechanism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Leader Bhattarai further asserted that the prevailing ultra-conservative party politics had also polluted the intellectual community capable of wisely guiding the country towards prosperity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"The parliamentary system has been synonymous to instability, horse-trading, internal betrayals and the culture of corruption,\" Dr Bhattarai argued, adding, \"It has already been proven that the parliamentary system in Nepals context is inappropriate, we are still to test other systems.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to him, UCPN (Maoist), CPN (UML) among other parties had sought votes during the CA election by supporting an arrangement for an executive head. A big faction in the Nepali Congress was also in favour of the same system.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/singha-durbar.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-26 01:34:58",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18872"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18525,
                        "title": "Election Commission recommends at least three percent threshold",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ballet.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-18526\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ballet.png\" alt=\"ballet\" width=\"586\" height=\"387\" /></a>The Election Commission (EC) has suggested a provision of at least three percent threshold in the first-past-the-post election system to secure proportional quota for the political parties after the new constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Furnishing a 20-point suggestion on the draft constitution on Sunday, the EC also recommended the Constituent Assembly to fix the date of the election to the local bodies within six months of the promulgation of the new constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The CA is also suggested to mention in the constitution the dates of the election to the President, Vice-President, federal parliament and the provincial assembly, or the EC given authroity to fix dates for these election with the consultation of the govenrment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Under the FPTP, the EC suggests one candidate should not be allowed to file candidacies from two constituencies. The women, indigenous, Dalit, Madhesi, and marginalized communities must be prioritized as the FPTP candidates.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Similarly, the EC has sought authority to fix the age eligible for casting votes and prepare the oters lists in the country and abroad.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It has also demanded authority to annouce the date of the local elections.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Other important suggestions include that appoitment of the officials in the EC should be made based on inclusivity and the professional competence, while the eligible age for anyone to be appointed as Chief Election Commisisoner and Election Commissioner should be fixed at 45 years and above.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In order for any political groups to be registered as the political party, it should submit its annual auditing report to the EC; and the election for the ward chairman should adopt the FPTP system.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ballet.png",
                        "date": "2015-07-19 15:54:05",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18525"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18393,
                        "title": "Hindus seek withdrawal of sexually explicit mandala from Toronto gallery",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-17887\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg\" alt=\"zed8-300x178\" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" /></a>Hindus want “Sacred Circle VI” mandala mosaic withdrawn from John B. Aird Gallery run in a government building in Toronto, indicating that it trivializes Hinduism and was highly inappropriate.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada today, said that mandala was a sacred symbolic drawing in Hinduism and was used for establishing a sacred space. Assembling pornographic images of women in a mandala was disturbing for the Hindus, as many times mandalas contained images of deities Hindus worshipped.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, stated that Ontario Government should not be in the business of promoting pornography and hurting the feelings of the devotees. Explicit and graphic sex acts displayed under the pretext of “sacred” happening just steps away from Legislative Assembly of Ontario and in a government building was really shocking.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed urged Ontario Premier Kathleen Wynne to intervene in the withdrawal of this objectionable mandala mosaic from the Gallery.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zed noted that Hindu concepts and symbols were not meant to be thrown around loosely in reimagined versions for dramatic effects in art galleries. Such absurd depiction of mandala with no scriptural backing was hurtful to the devotees.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed stressed that Hindus were for free expression as much as anybody else if not more. But faith was something sacred and attempts at belittling it tormented the devotees. Art galleries should be more sensitive while handling faith related subjects, Zed added.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hindus welcomed galleries and artists to immerse in Hinduism but taking it seriously, respectfully and responsibly and not just for indecorous showing of Hindu symbols and concepts to advance their selfish agenda. Casual flirting sometimes resulted in pillaging serious spiritual doctrines and revered symbols and hurting the devotees, Zed pointed out.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed further said that Hinduism was the oldest and third largest religion of the world with about one billion adherents and a rich philosophical thought and it should not be taken frivolously. No faith, larger or smaller, should be ridiculed at; Zed said and added that if galleries needed any assistance about Hinduism, he or other Hindu scholars would be glad to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mandala represents cosmos/universe and is a way of manifesting deity/deities, finding mention in Agamas and Tantras.  It represents the abode of the deity/deities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Sacred Circle VI” by Rosalie H. Maheux is part of Gallery’s \"30 UNDER 30 Exhibition\" (curated by Gary Michael Dault) running till <span data-term=\"goog_18633551\">July 24</span>. The Government of Ontario provides the exhibition space and related building services for Toronto’s John B. Aird Gallery, opened in 1985 and which claims to provide a \"nurturing atmosphere\".</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Jowenne Herrera and Sarah Morison are Gallery Board’s co-presidents, while Carla Garnet is the Executive Director.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x17811.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-18 06:31:34",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18393"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18361,
                        "title": "Dahal calls on Indian Prez, discusses statue-drafting, bilateral relations",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Pranab-Mukherjee102.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-18362\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Pranab-Mukherjee102.jpg\" alt=\"Pranab-Mukherjee102\" width=\"200\" height=\"226\" /></a>UCPN (Maoist) Chair Pushpa Kamal Dahal, who is presently on India visit, Friday called on Pranab Mukherjee, the President of India. During the meeting held this evening, matters relating to Nepals constitution writing process and Nepal-India bilateral relations were discussed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On the occasion, President Mukherjee praised Nepal’s political parties for their success in framing the first draft of the constitution being based on the 16-point agreement and taking the document to the public sphere for people’s submissions, according to Dahals aide Shiva Khakurel who is accompanying him.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Leader Dahal briefed the Indian President about the situation the political parties went through while preparing the new constitution’s draft. He was suggested by the Indian President not to give any one chance to complain that their voices were unheard while finalisng the draft of the constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In response, UCPN (M) Chair Dahal said the party was ready to promulgate the new constitution at the consent of all parties, pledging to address the sentiments of entire sections in the new constitution</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Pranab-Mukherjee102.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-18 02:36:49",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18361"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18284,
                        "title": "I do not hold DV, PR of any foreign country: Minister Dr Rijal",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/minendra-rijal_20140423083510.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-6193\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/minendra-rijal_20140423083510-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"minendra-rijal_20140423083510\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>Minister for Information and Communications, Dr Minendra Rijal, has said he does not hold Diversity Visa or Permanent Residency of any foreign country.Taking special time with the Speaker at the Legislature-Parliament meeting on Thursday, Minister Dr Rijal said, \"Im a Nepali citizen, Im permanent resident. Ive no DV, PR of any country, and neither any permit documents from the foreign countries.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr Rijal argued that he put forth such view in the Legislature-Parliament as the parliament members were accountable to the people. \"The social media, some weeklies and news portals mentioned my name as the person holding DV, PR though the parliament and its committee have not talked anything about it,\" he said, adding \"I think it is not good to spread such rumours. Were responsible to the people. Our responsibility to the people is through the parliament. And as a parliamentarian raised this issue without mentioning the name of the rumoured holders of the foreign DV, PR, I took it as an opportunity to respond to it now.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minister Rijal also said he had made his views public through the social media on this matter. The Minister reminded that he stayed in the US for nine years and came with flying colours in the MBA result, and got Graduate Student Achievement Award.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Moreover, he said the Wall Street Journal had conferred him the Graduate Student Achievement Award the same year. After conferring the award, Minister Dr Rijal said, the journal had written, \"See the names of these students written with tiny letter/font. Youll see these names in big sized letter in future.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Information Minister said, \"I had an opportunity of working abroad, I worked as a trainer in America and later as a guest lecturer in New York University for three years, but I did not choose to remain there and seek a career.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stating that earlier in his life he had the opportunity to work in proximity with BP Koirala during the years in student politics, the Minister further said that he had harbored the sentiment of working in Nepal, doing politics in Nepal and giving his utmost for contribution to Nepals democratic uprising.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minister Rijal said he thought it would be appropriate for him to inform the Nepali people through the parliament of his choice to serve the Nepali people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"In 1989 Americas economy was weak, while Japanese economy moved forward in strength,\" Minister Rijal said adding, \"A newspaper had written, there was a great competition to come to the US from various countries and no country remained aloof of this trend, there had been various reasons being written on this, and my name was in it, I am not saying these things to praise myself.\"</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/minendra2_20141207034019_20141207041133.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-16 16:38:51",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18284"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18245,
                        "title": "Hindus worldwide perturbed on India’s failure at containing frequent stampedes",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article41681.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-18246\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article41681-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"article41681\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Shocked and dismayed at the July 14 stampede in Rajahmundry district of Andhra Pradesh (India) reportedly killing dozens of pilgrims and injuring many, Hindus worldwide are highly critical of frequent occurrences of deadly stampedes at religious gatherings in India.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada (USA) today, said that although India was on track to become a global power but it could not even handle a domestic event properly and had yet to come up with a foolproof plan to manage large crowds.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">India failed or refused to learn lessons from the previous stampedes as these continued to happen. It was blight on a country, which prided itself on having joined the league of hottest growth economies, Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, pointed out while expressing grief over the loss of lives at July 14 stampede.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed further said: Our hearts and thoughts go out for the victims and their families and we are all in shock and anguish over this unimaginable loss. He called for prayers for the victims of the tragedy and their families.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zed indicated that it clearly reflected on India and Andhra Pradesh governments who appeared to have failed to properly manage a popular festival.Rajan Zed asked for apology from Andhra Pradesh government for failure to prevent this preventable tragedy, adequate compensation for the affected and their families, proper medical care for the injured and action against the negligent officials.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">India should better manage its festivals as stampedes were relatively common at India’s religious gatherings where large crowds gathered in small areas with very little or no crowd-control or safety measures, Zed added.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This stampede happened on Godavari river banks on the opening morning of the 12-day major religious festival known as Maha Pushkaralu, which comes once in 144 years, in which about 24 million pilgrims were expected to participate and take a holy dip, reports suggest.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article41681.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-16 08:23:36",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18245"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18241,
                        "title": "“Hindu Puja Room” at Phillips Exeter Academy ",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The prestigious Phillips Exeter Academy (PEA) in New Hampshire (USA) has a Hindu Puja Room in which hour-long Hindu puja (prayer) is held <span data-term=\"goog_1668109776\">on Sunday</span> evenings which is open to all PEA community.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/puja.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18242\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/puja.jpg\" alt=\"puja\" width=\"839\" height=\"508\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Holi is also celebrated on the campus and it hosts a Diwali dinner, reports suggest.Applauding PEA for provision of “Hindu Puja Room”, distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada (USA) today, described it as a step in the positive direction. Zed commended PEA for recognizing the intersection of spirituality and education, which was important in Hinduism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, urged all USA universities, colleges and residential schools; both public and private; to respond to the spiritual needs of diverse student body and provide permanent and dedicated Hindu prayer/meditation room for rituals, quiet reflection, festivals and spiritual exercise. It would help in the personal growth of Hindu students who were present in substantial numbers on various campuses. It was important to meet the spiritual needs of these students, Zed added.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed suggested that these Hindu prayer rooms should have an altar containing murtis (statues) of popular Hindu deities like Shiva, Vishnu, Rama, Krishna, Durga, Venkateshwara, Ganesha, Murugan, Saraswati, Hanuman, Lakshmi, Kali, etc.; besides being equipped with ghanta (big metallic bell hanging from the ceiling), dholak (two-headed hand-drum), Shiva-linga, etc. He or other Hindu scholars would be glad to help, if asked, regarding the structure of “Hindu Prayer Room”, Zed indicated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Phillips Exeter Academy, a co-educational residential school founded in 1781 and serving over 1000 students, offers over 400 courses on a 671 acres campus in Exeter. It claims to teach students to \"combine knowledge with goodness\" and its tuition for boarding students is $46,905 and operating budget $93 million. Thompson Hutton and Thomas E. Hassan are Trustees President and Principal respectively and its alumni include Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg, 14th US President Franklin Pierce, statesman Daniel Webster and writer Gore Vidal.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hinduism, oldest and third largest religion of the world, has about one billion adherents and moksh (liberation) is its ultimate goal. There are about three million Hindus in USA.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/puja.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-16 08:12:08",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18241"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18216,
                        "title": "North Carolina to have Hindu Temple on 7.6 acres",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Indianapolis-Hindu-temple-300x300.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-18217\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Indianapolis-Hindu-temple-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Indianapolis-Hindu-temple-300x300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>North Carolina will have another “traditional” Hindu temple in the near future.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ground Breaking Ceremony (Bhoomi Puja) for “Winston Salem Hindu Temple” in Clemmons (North Carolina) was held on<span data-term=\"goog_1340815287\">June 11</span>; which included pujas, aaradhana, havan, kalasha pradakshina, samprokshnas, etc. Besides worship services, this 3,600-square-foot Temple will also organize festivals, celebrations, special events, etc., and besides sanctuary, will also include classrooms and a community center, reports suggest.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To be built by Om Hindu Organization of North Carolina and Sri Mata Shaktipeetham, 7.6 acres have reportedly been purchased for this purpose. Construction, after consultations with temple architects in India, will start later this year. Meanwhile, distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada today, commended efforts of Temple leaders and area community for realizing this Hindu temple complex.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, further said that it was important to pass on Hindu spirituality, concepts and traditions to coming generations amidst so many distractions in the consumerist society and hoped that this new Temple would help in this direction. Zed stressed that instead of running after materialism; we should focus on inner search and realization of Self and work towards achieving moksh (liberation), which was the goal of Hinduism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It plans to have the shrines of Lalithaambika, Kaameshwara, Ganapathy, Balaji, Aditya, Shirdi Sai, Ram Parivar, Radha Krishna, Valli-Devasena-Subrahmanya, Ayyappa, Hanuman, Dhanvantri, and Navagraha; besides a Dwaja Sthambam. Estimated Cost for Lalithaambika shrine at $75,000 is highest among all of the shrines.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This will be the first Hindu temple of Forsyth County, where about 500 Hindu families reside. In the absence of a temple, the area Hindus have been travelling to Charlotte and Cary, besides worshipping at home shrines.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“A Hindu Temple stands for Tranquility, Education, Meditation, Purification, Love and Engagement”, according to Temple website. Dr. Sudhakar Pandit, Swami Rajendran and Krishna Surabhi are Chairman, Vice Chairman and Secretary respectively.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hinduism, oldest and third largest religion of the world, has about one billion adherents. There are about three million Hindus in USA.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Indianapolis-Hindu-temple-300x300.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-16 05:21:58",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18216"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 18140,
                        "title": "Government unveils Rs 819 billion budget for F/Y 2015/16",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The government has unveiled a budget of Rs 819.46 billion for the Fiscal Year 2015/016.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minister for Finance Dr Ram Sharan Mahat in the budget speech mentioned that of the total budget, Rs 484.26 was allocated for the current expenditure and Rs 208.87 billion for the capital expenditure. Similarly, for the financial management, Rs 126.32 billion has been allocated.<a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ram-ba.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-18141\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ram-ba-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"ram ba\" width=\"839\" height=\"600\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The expenditure estimates for the upcoming Fiscal Year is more by 32 percent while revised estimate is more by 56.8 percent compared to the current Fiscal Year.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Among the sources to bear the expenses for the coming Fiscal Year, the revenue will bear Rs 475 billion, while repayment of debt principal Rs 200 billion, foreign grants Rs 110.92 billion. But, there will be the deficit of Rs 231 billion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In order to address the deficit budget, Rs 88 billion will be generated from the internal loan, and Rs 48. 56 billion from the cash reserve.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ram-ba.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-14 16:15:25",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/18140"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17994,
                        "title": "Hindus seek prayer services at chapels of world’s airports",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hindus are urging Hindu prayer services at the world’s airports which have chapels.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/interfaith-airport-chapel-hartsfield-jackson-atlanta-international-airport.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17995\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/interfaith-airport-chapel-hartsfield-jackson-atlanta-international-airport.jpg\" alt=\"interfaith-airport-chapel-hartsfield-jackson-atlanta-international-airport\" width=\"824\" height=\"518\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Where airports provide facilities for specific religious groups, like John F. Kennedy International Airport in New York and Frankfurt Airport in Germany, Hindus would also like a designated “Hindu Prayer Room”.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada today, said that a lot of Hindu passengers daily used world’s airports and it would be nice if airports offered Hindu services or a quiet facility at the airport where they could pray/meditate/worship and perform religious services.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, urged world airport authorities to work in this direction as an issue of fairness and equality in customer service. He or other Hindu scholars would be glad to help, if asked, regarding the structure of “Hindu Prayer Room”.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hindus would appreciate if this “Hindu Prayer Room” had murtis (statues) of popular deities, copies of sacred scriptures, a traditional bell and recorded devotional music; and once-a-week kirtan and arti session was held in it, Rajan Zed noted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prayer/worship to God was highly important in Hinduism, oldest and third largest religion of the world with about one billion adherents, and it would be great to have Hindu prayer service or “Hindu Prayer Room” at airports so that Hindu passengers did not miss their daily worship rituals/rites while travelling through; which might include recitation of texts, repetition of mantras and dhayan (meditation), Zed added.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to Pew Research Center (PRC), \"a nonpartisan fact tank\" headquartered in Washington DC, “Most of the busiest U.S. airports have dedicated chapels” (first being Our Lady of the Airways, opened at Boston’s Logan International Airport about 60 years ago) and “many of these facilities offer a variety of worship services for different faith traditions”. John F. Kennedy International Airport in New York “has four places of worship: a Catholic church, a Protestant chapel, a mosque and a synagogue”, while “Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport, meanwhile, has five different interfaith chapels – one in every terminal”. “Washington Dulles International Airport, near Washington, D.C., offers weekly Catholic Mass, Protestant worship and Christian prayer services, as well as daily Jewish and Muslim prayer services”, PRC write-up adds.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/interfaith-airport-chapel-hartsfield-jackson-atlanta-international-airport.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-13 10:34:49",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17994"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17885,
                        "title": "Former pub being converted to Hindu temple in England",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-11171\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x178.jpg\" alt=\"zed\" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" /></a>Former pub in Acle in Norfolk county of East England is poised to become a Hindu temple.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to reports, official permission is being sought to convert this former pub into a Hindu temple and an offer has been submitted to the Broads Authority, the agency responsible for the Broads where the site is located. Building will be remodeled for usage as a Hindu temple and to give it a Hindu appearance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Between Norwich and Great Yarmouth, this proposed temple building is one of the most distinctive locations in the area. Originally a popular pub called the “Stracey Arms”, it became “Three Feathers”, then converting to an American-style bar and grill diner “Pontiac Roadhouse”, and later becoming a Chinese takeaway and then a Spanish restaurant “Embrujo”, reports suggest.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Meanwhile, distinguished Hindu statesman Rajan Zed, in a statement in Nevada (USA) today, commended efforts of temple leaders and area community for efforts to realize this Hindu temple complex.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rajan Zed, who is President of Universal Society of Hinduism, further said that it was important to pass on Hindu spirituality, concepts and traditions to coming generations amidst so many distractions in the consumerist society and hoped that this new temple would help in this direction. Zed stressed that instead of running after materialism; we should focus on inner search and realization of Self and work towards achieving moksh (liberation), which was the goal of Hinduism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Besides the sanctuary for worship, prayers and rituals; this proposed temple would also serve as meeting venue for the area Hindus; hold various functions and festivals; organize yoga and meditation classes, workshops, havans, activities for children and seniors, community events, cultural and educational activities; raise a multi-purpose library; etc.; per reports.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vedic Cultural society of East Anglia has been formed for this purpose, which is working towards its registration as a charity. Dr. Devender Khorana is one of the leaders of this temple move. Area Hindus have been reportedly meeting at Roman Catholic Parish of St Mary in Great Yarmouth for the last about 14 years.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hinduism, oldest and third largest religion of the world, has about one billion adherents.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/zed8-300x1781.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-12 10:06:20",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17885"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17805,
                        "title": "Teams leave for villages with draft constitution",
                        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Constitution-of-Nepal_20150708074043.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Constitution-of-Nepal_20150708074043-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Constitution-of-Nepal_20150708074043\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-17806\" /></a>The Constituent Assembly Secretariat staffs have left for villages with the preliminary draft of the new constitution to seek peoples feedback. \r\n\r\nThe staffs left for all 240 constituencies across 75 districts with the draft constitution and gazette to participate in the extensive interaction and meetings aimed at collecting peoples feedbacks scheduled for July 20 and 21. \r\n\r\nA total of 41 teams tasked with collecting suggestions from the people left the capital city on Saturday alone, while more teams will leave on Sunday for mountainous regions, CA Secretariat Joint Spokesperson Sudarshan Kuinkel told the National News Agency (RSS). Two employees are in each team.",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Constitution-of-Nepal_20150708074043.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-12 02:18:45",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17805"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17775,
                        "title": "Phuyal elected chair of Parliamentary Affairs Journalist Society",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/rajrndra.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-17776\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/rajrndra-300x300.jpeg\" alt=\"rajrndra\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>Rajendra Phuyal was elected the chair of Parliamentary Affairs Journalist Society today.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A gathering of journalists associated with the Society elected Phuyal as the chair. Similarly, Ishwori Subedi was elected as vice-chair, Babin Sharma as general secretary and Ashok Dahal as the secretary. Likewise, Sanjeev Bagale was picked as the treasurer of the Society.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Likewise, other members of the Society include Lucky Chaudhary, Deepesh Shrestha, Rojina Thapa, Mukti Regmi, Ananta Anurag, Deepak Acharya, Manoj Satyal and Satish Subedi.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A vice-chair and secretary under woman quota would be nominated by a full meeting of the Society.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/rajrndra.jpeg",
                        "date": "2015-07-11 11:13:46",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17775"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17744,
                        "title": "Budhigandaki Hydro Project would be constructed at any cost: PM Koirala (Video)",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prime Minister Sushil Koirala has said that the Budhigandaki Hydropower Project would be constructed at any cost. Talking to a delegation comprising leaders of different political parties from Gorkha and Dhading districts at his official residence in Baluwatar this morning, PM Koirala said that the project would be included in the new budget. The delegation met the PM for drawing his attention for immediate beginning of the project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On the occasion, PM Koirala directed Finance Minister Dr Ram Sharan Mahat and Energy Minister Radha Kumari Gyawali to take necessary actions in this regard. The delegation led by Nepali Congress Chief Whip Chinkaji Shrestha urged the PM to take initiation for the immediate construction of the project, as it was included in the policy and programmes of the government as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Budhigandaki Hydropower Project is included as the national pride project and it should be constructed with utmost priority, said the delegation team. On the occasion, the politicians from the affected two districts urged the government to make arrangements of the resettlement of the people of the affected areas by providing due compensation of the land. The Detailed Project Report (DPR) of the 1,200 MW Project has reached in the final phase, it is said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A French company, which has been carrying out the DPR, said that it was slightly delayed to submit the report due to the devastating quake. The Company has hinted at the possibility of shifting the affected people at Seurenitar of Gorkha. During the meeting, the delegation team also asked the PM to intensify the resettlement projects, reconstruction of historical, religious, cultural heritages and other developmental projects in the worst quake-hit areas in these districts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Politicians Rajendra Prasad Pandey, Guru Prasad Burlakoti, Parashu Ram Tamang, Dhan Bahadur Ghale, Dilman Pakhrin and other local leaders of different political parties were present on the occasion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WH87X0IEDRY\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Former Prime minister Dr. Baburam Bhattrai Speech about Budigandaki  </strong></a>\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WH87X0IEDRY\" width=\"839\" height=\"550\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>Former Deputy Primeminister : Narayan Kaji Shrestha </strong>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uwZIF4TDuqk\" width=\"839\" height=\"550\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/budigandaki.png",
                        "date": "2015-07-11 09:22:08",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17744"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17508,
                        "title": "Proposal to take draft constitution to people endorsed, 15 days for peoples feedback",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/sambidhan.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-621\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/sambidhan.jpg\" alt=\"sambidhan\" width=\"267\" height=\"189\" /></a>The Constituent Assembly meeting on Tuesday evening endorsed the proposal seeking the publication of the draft of the Constitution of Nepal 2072 with the agreement in principle to take it to the people for feedback.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">CA Chairperson Subash Nembang presented the proposal for final decision after the Constitution Drafting Committee Chairman Krishna Prasad Sitaula responded to the issues raised during the deliberation. The proposal was endorsed unanimously.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As some CA members tried to object the process, CA Chair Nembang urged them to discuss the dissents at the Constitutional Political Dialogue and Consensus Committee as the arrangement for was made there.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A separate proposal presented by Constitution Drafting Committees Chair Krishna Prasad Sitaula on publicity of the first draft and assigning the Civic Relations and Advisory Committee for it with 15 days term was also endorsed by the meeting.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nepal Workers and Peasants Partys Dilli Prasad Kafle made objection over the 15 day time allocated for drawing feedback from the people reasoning it was a short period.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>No doubt on constitution now: CDC Chairman Sitaula</strong></em>\r\nCDC Chairman Sitaula said the Committee was ready to take the constitutions draft to the peoples domain for their feedback in accordance with the spirit and sentiments of the Comprehensive Peace Agreement. There was no doubt over the promulgation of the new constitution along with guarantee of federalism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Committee had the support and cooperation from the entire CA and political parties in course of preparing the draft, he said, pledging to owning up suggestions given in the discussions to produce the best constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It was in a view that introducing a proposal for going with referendum to take decisions on the matters of republic or federalism was irrelevant as none could go with a process of reversing the changes brought out by the historic Peoples Movement, according to him.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But still a two-third majority in the parliament can make amendments to the articles of the constitution except those relating to peoples sovereignty.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"Some may enjoy while engaging in the talks about the possibility of the restoration of monarchy but it is worthless to spend times in such impossible matter. Lets stop to talk about monarchy as the constitution is not a document to reverse changes, rather it is the means of institutionalising them and former King Gyanendra has already accepted the decisions of the first CA,\" he reiterated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Recalling the late Girija Prasad Koirala, one of the precursors of the peace process on this occasion, leader Sitaula said he was happy to see all the signatories of the peace process into a common forum.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sitaula opined that although issues relating to the structure of the State, form of governance and federalism could be addressed in the draft through amendment, sensitive issues concerning citizenship should be furthered with due homework.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"The decision on citizenship should be made taking into account the geographical and geo-political status of the country,\" he argued.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As for federalism, President Situala clarified that the draft had the provision that while federalizing the country, it will be based on the proportional representation of the geography and population for which the district and local bodies at community level could coordinate.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He further explained that the draft constitution has the provisions according to which there is the participation of at least four women including from the marginalised community in a village assembly.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As far as the judiciary system is concerned, he said that the first draft has incorporated the same provision as in the Interim Constitution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Mentioning that the judiciary was made independent, Sitaula said in case concerns were raised over the competency and morality of Judges, a permanent impeachment inquiry committee could be formed to look into the matter.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/sambidhan.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-07 16:41:00",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17508"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17486,
                        "title": "Floods sweep away three micro-hydel powerhouses",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Electricity supply at Mattim, Chhitapokhari, Khidima and Temma areas in Khotang was disrupted after the floods eliminated three powerhouses of the micro hydropower project in the district.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The recent floods occurred on Saturday night swept away the powerhouses of Tawakhola-III Micro Hydropower (17kw), Khobukhola Micro Hydropower (9.5kw) and Sanchahira Micro Hydropower Project (9kw), bringing the power generation to nil.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Treasurer of Tawakhola-III Micro Hydropower Project Yubraj Katawal said that as high as 243 households are left without electricity supply in Mattim and Chhitapokhari after the powerhouse of the project was wiped out in the flood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Likewise, nearly 175 households were also living without electricity supply in Khidima and Temma.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Locals said that equal time and cost would take for the reconstruction of the damaged powerhouses and resume power generation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Similarly, property worth Rs 4 million was damaged after the flood swept away Mewakhola Hydropower in the district, according project chief Lalit Kumar Rai. The project was expected to generate power within three month if the construction works were unhampered.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/khotang.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-07-07 10:47:38",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/17486"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 17107,
                        "title": "Dhakal elected chair of NAFEA",
                        "content": "<a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/bimal-dhakal.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-17109\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/bimal-dhakal.jpg\" alt=\"bimal-dhakal\" width=\"200\" height=\"250\" /></a>Bimal Dhakal has been elected the Chairperson of Nepal Association of Foreign Employment Agencies.\r\nDhakal secured 237 votes against 213 of his arch-rival Saroj Kumar Pokharel. He had filed candidacy from the Democratic Foreign Employment Forum.\r\nAmong other elected are Kumud Khanal (first vice-chairperson), Hari Bahadur Pandey Chhetri (second chairperson), Muktinath Adhikari (third chairperson), Rohan Gurung (general secretary), Rajendra Bhandari (secretary) and Prateema Maharjan (treasurer).",
