                        "id": 16867,
                        "title": "13 passengers injured in Siraha bus accident",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As many as 13 passengers were injured after a bus met with an accident at Mirchaiya Municipality of Siraha district, today.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to the Area Police Office, Mirchaiya, the bus (Na 3 Kha 2257) left from Katari met with an accident after the driver lost control of the vehicle.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All the injured have been rushed to Rekha Nurshing Home, Mirchaiya, and they are reported to be out of danger, said Police Inspector Hari Khatiwada. Police have been searching for the absconding bus driver for legal action, he said.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/siraha.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-30 11:02:32",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16867"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16757,
                        "title": "Veteran Indian journalist Ramashish passes away",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Veteran Indian journalist Ramashish on Monday succumbed to fatal injuries which he sustained in a road accident on June 12 after being rammed by a speeding bicycle at Sitamadhi of Bihar in India.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ramashish.jpeg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16758\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ramashish.jpeg\" alt=\"ramashish\" width=\"829\" height=\"547\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ramashish died at 10 am on Monday while undergoing treatment at Himal Hospital in Kamal Pokhari, Kathmandu at the age of 79.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The veteran journalist, who was born in India, had been writing for the last 46 years in Nepal. He was working as a correspondent of the Hindustan Samachar, an Indian news agency.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ramashish with an intimate knowledge of Nepal-India relations has interviewed top Nepali political figures including Bishweshwor Prasad Koirala, Ganeshman Singh, Krishna Prasad Bhattarai, Girija Prasad Koirala and Mahendra Narayan Nidhi.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Journalist Ramashish was expelled from the country after he wrote news on the fire that broke out at Singha Durbar during the rule of King Mahendra Shah. Ramashish was repeatedly jailed during the peoples uprising in 1990.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Ramashishs grandson Bhaskar told the National News Agency (RSS) that the journalists mortal remains will be cremated on Tuesday at Surukhand in Sitamadhi of Bihar in India.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/ramashish.jpeg",
                        "date": "2015-06-29 15:42:06",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16757"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16729,
                        "title": "Foreigners promoting Nepal’s tourism",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At a time when the number of tourist is decreasing after the devastating earthquake, the Annapurna Conservation Area Project (ACAP) has launched a campaign to disseminate the message that Nepal is safe for visitors.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Nepal-–-Mustang-Trekking-3.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16730\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Nepal-–-Mustang-Trekking-3.jpg\" alt=\"Nepal-–-Mustang-Trekking-3\" width=\"839\" height=\"566\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ACAP has arranged a visit for geologists, engineers and media persons from Belgium, USA and Germany in different areas of its districts in Mustang, Myagdi, Lamjung, Kaski and Manang.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Likewise, interactions were organised with the participation of local women’s groups, tourism entrepreneurs, politicians and management of the conservation management committees and stakeholders, said a representative of ACAP Paras Singh.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“The foreigners were highly excited for this campaign. They would spread positive messages in their countries,” Singh said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is no alternative to unite for the revival of tourism of this area, he added. The teams have also working to identify alternative routes to Manang and Mustang for tourism and trekking promotion.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/Nepal-–-Mustang-Trekking-3.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-29 10:25:46",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16729"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16584,
                        "title": "Himalayan honeybees decreasing",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As the beehives of the Apis laboriosa bee known as Himalayan honeybees decreased gradually, production of honey too has come down in the recent days. The honey of the Himalayan honeybees is famous for its better taste and Ayurvedic importance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article-0-1C6B3C7500000578-948_964x635.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16585\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article-0-1C6B3C7500000578-948_964x635.jpg\" alt=\"article-0-1C6B3C7500000578-948_964x635\" width=\"834\" height=\"555\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Likewise, the practice of collecting the sweet stuff is dying out as the bees slowly become extinct.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is said that the Apis laboriosa bee, the world’s largest bee, have started to migrate from their origins in Chimkhola, Ramche and Pakhapani in Myagdi district.\r\nThe gradual extinction of the Himalayan honeybee has made the locals much worried, Tirthaman Pun, a local of Chimkhola said. There used to be as high as 25 hives until some years ago but now there are only seven or eight hives, the honey hunter said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Climate change and increased human activities are blamed for the gradual extinction of the Himalayan honeybee. Likewise, human interference and maximum use of chemical fertilisers also pose threats to the bees that mostly make their hives in the steep cliffs.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Locals said that the precious nectar of the Himalayan honeybee is also used as the medicine to cure the bones diseases as well as to increase the sex power.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/article-0-1C6B3C7500000578-948_964x635.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-28 10:17:06",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16584"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16527,
                        "title": "5.6-magnitude earthquake strikes Assam ",
                        "content": "<strong><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/5-6-magnitude-earthquake-strikes-assam.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-16528\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/5-6-magnitude-earthquake-strikes-assam.jpg\" alt=\"5-6-magnitude-earthquake-strikes-assam\" width=\"310\" height=\"233\" /></a>no damage reported so far</strong>\r\n\r\nAn earthquake of moderate intensity of 5.6 on the Richter Scale rocked <a href=\"http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/5-6-magnitude-earthquake-strikes-assam-no-damage-reported-so-far/articleshow/47849304.cms\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Assam</strong></a>, including its capital Guwahati, at 6.35 am today.\r\n\r\nThe epicentre of the tremor was in Kokrajhar at a depth of 10 km on latitude 26.5 degree north and longitude 90.1 degree east, MET officials said.\r\n\r\nThe quake rattled doors and windows forcing people to rush out of their houses, police said. There was no immediate report of any loss of life or damage to property, they said.",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/5-6-magnitude-earthquake-strikes-assam.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-28 05:55:38",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16527"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16472,
                        "title": "Grade 11 exams end peacefully, HSEB says",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/hseb.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-16473\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/hseb.jpg\" alt=\"hseb\" width=\"230\" height=\"250\" /></a>The examinations of grade 11 in 68 districts conducted by the Higher Secondary Education Board (HSEB) completed today.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vice-chairman of the HSEB, Chaitanya Sharma, said that the exams were held peacefully in all districts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Meanwhile, the exams of grade 12 would start on Monday while the exams of grade 11 would begin from July 9 in worst quake-hit districts namely Gorkha, Dhading, Nuwakot, Kavre, Sindhupalchowk, Dolakha and Ramechhap .</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/hseb.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-27 11:23:38",
