                    {
                        "id": 16447,
                        "title": "288 families at risk of landslide in Nuwakot",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/village_20120905085526.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-16448\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/village_20120905085526.jpg\" alt=\"village_20120905085526\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" /></a>A total of 288 families in constituency no.3 of Nuwakot are at risk of landslide due to the impact of the April 25 earthquake.The district-level task force including geologists and engineers carried out a field study of the area covering one municipality and 18 VDCs and recommended to the district natural calamity committee for translocation of the settlements, according to chief of the district soil conservation office in Nuwakot Shyam Sundar Shrestha.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A report by the team points out that the Nepal telecom tower, irrigation canal and arable land in ward nos-7 and 9 of Fikuri VDC are at risk of being hit by landslides from above the hills. As the rainy season has already started, the government should immediately resettle the households at risk, Shrestha said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Similar field study in constituencies nos 1 and 2 of the district will also be carried out soon on the basis of the application received for the same from the locals, said assistant CDO Khagendra Ghimire.</p>",
                        "img": "http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/village_20120905085526.jpg",
                        "date": "2015-06-27 08:13:40",
                        "link": "http://www.newsnrn.com/api/public/v1/news/16447"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 16397,
                        "title": "Statute’s preliminary draft presented to CDC, deliberations from tomorrow",
                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/sambidhan.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-621\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/sambidhan.jpg\" alt=\"sambidhan\" width=\"267\" height=\"189\" /></a>A preliminary draft of the constitution has presented at the meeting of Constitution Drafting Committee (CDC) held late this night.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The draft was prepared by the preliminary integrated drafting taskforce formed by the Committee. The copies of draft have been provided to committee members for study and deliberations on it will take place in a Committee meeting to be held in Singha Durbar tomorrow.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The final draft will be submitted to the Constituent Assembly (CA) Chairman for discussions in the CA meeting to take place on coming June 29.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The 121-page preliminary draft prepared in line with the 16-point agreement reached among four major political forces has 37 parts and 296 articles, including seven annex</p>",
