                        "content": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The number of people killed in landslide occurred at Lumle, Bhadaure Tamagi and Thulichour of Dhikurpokhari VDC-9 in Kaski district on Wednesday night following heavy rainfall has so far reached 30.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/kaski4.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-19175\" src=\"http://www.newsnrn.com/wp-content/uploads/kaski4.jpg\" alt=\"kaski\" width=\"839\" height=\"500\" /></a></p>\r\nAccording to the District Police Office, Kaski, a total of 23 people died at Lumle, five at Bhadaure Tamagi and two at Thulichour of Dhikurpokhari.\r\n\r\nOf the deceased, 12 are men and 18 women. Similarly, a total of 18 people were injured in the incident. Of them, 14 were injured at Bhadaure Tamagi, three at Lumle and one at Dhikurpokhari, said police.",
